Cell["\<\
Field score of each strategy at four noise levels. At \[Epsilon]=0 the \
generous reciprocators lead; the extortioner (ZD-Extort-2) finishes last.\
\>", "Text",
 CellMargins->{{70, 70}, {2, 14}},
 FontSize->11,
 FontSlant->Italic,
 FontColor->GrayLevel[
  0.35],ExpressionUUID->"aad478f8-af3e-4905-b413-b6138f3497f1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["The classic lesson holds.",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " Nice, reciprocal, forgiving strategies dominate. Notably, plain \
Tit-for-Tat is ",
 StyleBox["edged out",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " by its more forgiving cousins \[Dash] Generous TFT and Tit-for-2-Tats \
\[Dash] exactly the refinement Axelrod found in his second tournament. And \
the zero-determinant ",
 StyleBox["extortioner finishes dead last",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": extortion wins individual matches but poisons the cooperative environment \
it depends on."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"df49cbff-68e7-492f-a7f1-3e62031d442e"],

Cell["The payoff structure of who-beats-whom:", "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"07591207-2c95-4fb1-bfa9-616734cf3b48"],

