Cell["\<\
As noise rises, every strategy's score is pulled toward the mutual-defection \
payoff P=1, and the gap between 'nice' and 'nasty' strategies narrows. \
Unforgiving strategies (Grim, Gradual) fall fastest: a single accidental \
defection traps them in retaliation.\
\>", "Text",
 CellMargins->{{70, 70}, {2, 14}},
 FontSize->11,
 FontSlant->Italic,
 FontColor->GrayLevel[
  0.35],ExpressionUUID->"bc4a72df-72ad-4a43-8e45-bf361fdf64cb"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
3. The evolutionary tournament \[Dash] the stable mix depends on noise\
\>", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"4e125a67-5be9-402e-874f-20d6e3bd6db7"],

Cell["\<\
Axelrod's deeper question was evolutionary: if successful strategies \
reproduce, which ones survive? We answer it two ways.\
\>", "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"a5fdc57e-25c0-46cf-bf3a-b828c2026d70"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Replicator dynamics", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"2cc86574-aaf9-4eeb-a2e7-39d6c708a07d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let ",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " be the vector of population fractions and ",
 StyleBox["A",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " the mean-payoff matrix (",
 StyleBox["A[i,j]",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " = score of ",
 StyleBox["i",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " against ",
 StyleBox["j",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 "). Each strategy grows in proportion to its fitness relative to the \
population average:"
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"e1906467-4cce-4bc3-bb40-181dbf72b98b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["x", "i"], "'", "=", 
   SubscriptBox["x", "i"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"A", ".", "x"}], ")"}], "i"], "-", 
     RowBox[{"x", ".", "A", ".", "x"}]}], ")"}]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 CellMargins->{{80, 50}, {8, 
  8}},ExpressionUUID->"d11d4ec4-615a-42b3-bc78-4de03db10f23"],

Cell["\<\
replicator[A_, steps_, mut_] := Module[{x = ConstantArray[1./n, n], f, phi},
  Do[ f = A . x; phi = x . f;
      x = x f / phi;              (* selection           *)
      x = (1 - mut) x + mut/n;    (* small mutation term  *)
      x = x / Total[x],
    {steps}];
  x]\
\>", "Input",
 CellMargins->{{60, 30}, {6, 6}},
 FontSize->11,ExpressionUUID->"7255070e-9b48-4228-b045-c8211d3469f0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Sweeping the noise level and recording the stable composition gives the \
headline figure (top of this post). It reveals ",
 StyleBox["three regimes",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ":"
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"cb251f3f-3102-4fa0-8d24-807a1a355674"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Low noise (\[Epsilon] \[TildeTilde] 0): ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "a coexistence of cooperative strategies \[Dash] Generous TFT, \
Tit-for-2-Tats, ZD-Generous, Tit-for-Tat and Pavlov share the population. \
Cooperation is evolutionarily robust."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d74e634a-da16-4a36-a62a-a5cda7624961"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Intermediate noise: ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "the forgiving reciprocators (Generous TFT, Tit-for-2-Tats, ZD-Generous) \
dominate and trade the lead among themselves \[Dash] error-correction is at a \
premium."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"dfd71034-b57b-4b57-82b9-5bdbb1cc867b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["High noise (\[Epsilon] \[GreaterEqual] 0.2): ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "cooperation collapses. AllD sweeps to ~99% of the population: under heavy \
noise, reciprocators spend so long accidentally punishing each other that \
unconditional defection becomes the only stable attractor."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"16bf89b1-b672-4da9-918b-da6207db7acd"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["A finite-population check: the Moran process", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"ae9c6c5d-e242-4d53-8a1d-770151196d01"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Replicator dynamics is a deterministic, infinite-population limit. To \
confirm the result is not an artefact of that idealisation, we also run a \
stochastic ",
 StyleBox["Moran process",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (population N=100, frequency-dependent birth-death with rare mutation) and \
record the long-run average composition."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"a0316adf-2d1b-411d-bb01-a1c5120c3f6b"],

