 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"4de70de1-39bb-4848-a0b0-c7fc2c4f5638"],

Cell["\<\
The discovered memory-one probabilities vs noise. The forgiveness parameter \
pCD (cooperate again after being suckered) rises with noise \[Dash] \
error-correction becomes essential \[Dash] until, at very high noise, the \
best response against a decaying field tilts back toward defection.\
\>", "Text",
 CellMargins->{{70, 70}, {2, 14}},
 FontSize->11,
 FontSlant->Italic,
 FontColor->GrayLevel[
  0.35],ExpressionUUID->"a92a0702-da54-4631-945e-95709697925c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is the same lesson as the evolutionary tournament, reached by a \
different route: ",
 StyleBox["the optimal behaviour is a function of the environment",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ", and noise is the knob that turns generous reciprocity into defection."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"1db31612-8bc5-4187-89e6-f0a8dd37a4ce"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["5. Conclusions", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"89406e93-9bbe-446b-8e7d-a7f960879467"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Tit-for-Tat is excellent but not optimal. ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "In a cooperative field, more forgiving reciprocators (Generous TFT, \
Tit-for-2-Tats) edge it out \[Dash] and extortion finishes last."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"05946a63-ba44-439d-9795-8f4c9b191007"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Evolutionary stability is noise-dependent. ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "Replicator and Moran dynamics agree: generous cooperation is stable at low \
noise; unconditional defection takes over at high noise."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"2dfb31e7-9b73-442b-973d-b3aecbc48681"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Forgiveness is the answer to noise. ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "Both the evolutionary winners and the algorithmically discovered strategies \
become more forgiving as noise rises \[Dash] up to the point where the whole \
field collapses."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"31a159ed-0465-47fc-867b-306678281a0d"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Reproducing this work", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"bc65ab0d-f64c-4473-a1dd-4dd9fba4811f"],

Cell["\<\
Everything here is a few seconds to a few minutes of Wolfram Language \[Dash] \
no external data, no API keys. The full source is on GitHub.\
\>", "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"5e025811-1a59-4934-b0a8-d231d49a999c"],

Cell["\<\
wolframscript -file tests/sanity.wls        # correctness checks
wolframscript -file wolfram/tournament.wls  # round-robin ranking
wolframscript -file wolfram/evolution.wls   # replicator + Moran vs noise
wolframscript -file wolfram/discover.wls     # strategy discovery
wolframscript -file wolfram/figures.wls      # regenerate all figures\
\>", "Program",
 CellMargins->{{60, 30}, {6, 6}},
 ShowStringCharacters->False,
 FontFamily->"Courier",
 FontSize->11,
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.95, 0.96, 0.98],ExpressionUUID->"50017d25-193b-41cc-8db8-4905d3f17cba"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Built entirely in the Wolfram Language. The \
strategy-discovery loop borrows the propose \[Rule] evaluate \[Rule] accept \
shape of automated-research scaffolds, re-implemented natively in WL.",
 FontSlant->Italic]], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"35a8dc20-dfb3-4eb5-9e64-3ec866366a0e"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
